[{"id":"VR005544","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents two diagrams labeled Figure A and Figure B. Figure A shows semicircular wave fronts equally spaced and concentric with two dots a horizontal distance S sub A equals 2 N lambda apart. There are 4 wave fronts drawn for each dot. A dashed vertical line is drawn at a position between the dots. Figure B shows semicircular wave fronts equally spaced and concentric with two dots a horizontal distance S sub B equals 3 N lambda apart. There are 4 wave fronts drawn for each dot. A dashed vertical line is drawn at a position between the dots.\" height=\"451\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR005544.g03.png\" width=\"300\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A beam of high-velocity electrons is aimed toward two different pairs of narrow slits. Each of the slits can be treated as a source of circular waves. The electron waves are represented in figures <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> by a set of semicircles that are spaced a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N lambda\"><math alttext=\"N lambda\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>N</mi><mi>λ</mi></mrow></math></span></span> apart. In figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, the sources are separated by a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s sub A equals 2 N lambda\"><math alttext=\"s sub A equals 2 N lambda\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>N</mi><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. In figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, the sources are separated by a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"s sub B equals 3 N lambda\"><math alttext=\"s sub B equals 3 N lambda\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>N</mi><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following describes the effect of a change in slit spacing on the interference pattern that can be observed on a distant screen?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR005544_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Decreasing the slit spacing decreases the spacing of the bright fringes on the screen.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Decreasing the slit spacing decreases the wavelength of the electrons that reach the screen.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Increasing the slit spacing decreases the spacing of the bright fringes on the screen.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Increasing the slit spacing decreases the wavelength of the electrons that reach the screen.</p>"],"answer":2}]